         </fn>
         <fn id="d8e155a1310">
            <label>2</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d8e162" publication-type="other">
ln conducting this study the impact of the tax system on 19 fields was analysed with the com-
puterised financial model. The results of all the tests referred to in this paper are fairly voluminous
and are not presented in detail here but are available from the authors on application.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d8e175a1310">
            <label>3</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d8e182" publication-type="other">
For a detailed and illuminating discussion of the effect of the safeguard and tapering provisions on
marginal rates see Report on the Government's Proposed Changes to the Petroleum Revenue Tax, UK Offshore
Operators Association, January, 1979.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d8e195a1310">
            <label>4</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d8e202" publication-type="other">
For a more detailed account of the effects of the taxation system see A G Kemp and D Cohen, The
Impact of the New System of Oil Taxation in the UK, Research Monograph, Fraser of Allander Institute,
Glasgow (forthcoming).</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d8e216a1310">
            <label>5</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d8e223" publication-type="other">
For a detailed analysis of the behaviour of Government revenue over the lifetime of fields see A G
Kemp and D Cohen, op. cit., (forthcoming).</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d8e233a1310">
            <label>6</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d8e240" publication-type="other">
It is interesting to note that in Norway where there is no formal ring fence as such that the fiscal
advantages of integrated operations are very much less. The main depreciation allowances can only
be utilised when production from a field commences. For elucidation of the system see Alexander G
Kemp and D Crichton 'North Sea Oil Taxation in Norway', Energy Economics, Vol 1, No 1, January,
1979.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
